{'type': 'chat', 'use_rag': True, 'message': 'Explain Spring Boot in simple terms', 'retrieved_count': 0, 'answer': '**What is Spring Boot?**\n\nSpring Boot is a framework that helps developers build web applications quickly and efficiently. It\'s built on top of the popular Spring Framework.\n\nThink of it like a toolbox for building web apps. You can use pre-built components, known as "starters," to include features like database connectivity, security, and more. This way, you don\'t have to start from scratch every time you build an app.\n\n**Key benefits:**\n\n1. **Faster development**: Spring Boot provides a set of defaults, so you don\'t need to spend hours configuring everything.\n2. **Simplified code**: Your code is cleaner and easier to read since you\'re using pre-built components.\n3. **Improved scalability**: Your apps can grow with your business needs.\n\nThat\'s the essence of Spring Boot in simple terms!', 'ts': 1771524209.4307263}
